== Land Use == === Water Systems and Fishing Ports === * Rivers: [[:en:Kuriyama River|Kuriyama River]] (Basin area: 292 km²), {{ill|Kidogawa River|ja|木戸川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kidogawa River|qq=|1=Kidogawa River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11518414}} (72 km²), {{ill|Sakuta River|ja|作田川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakuta River|qq=|1=Sakuta River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11385396}} (104 km²), {{ill|Makame River|ja|真丸川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Makame River|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (82 km²), {{ill|Nanjirogawa River|ja|南白鱗川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nanjirogawa River|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (116 km²), [[:en:Ichinomiya River|Ichinomiya River]] (222 km²) * Wetlands: Kuriyama River Wetlands ({{ill|Takohikari Wetlands|ja|多古光水原|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takohikari Wetlands|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), {{ill|Narutō-Tōgane Carnivorous Plant Community|ja|成東東金食虫植物群落|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Narutō-Tōgane Carnivorous Plant Community|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 成東・東金食虫植物群落|1=Naruto-Togane Area Carnivorous Plant Field|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11495489}}, {{ill|Mobara-Hachitsumi Wetlands|ja|茂原八積水原|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mobara-Hachitsumi Wetlands|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (disappeared) * {{ill|Lagoon|ja|海跡湖|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lagoon|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 湖沼|1=still waters|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q337567}}: {{ill|Tsubakiko|ja|椊海|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsubakiko|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (disappeared), {{ill|Kusayanuma|ja|乾草沼|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kusayanuma|qq=|1=Kusayanuma|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11370678}}, {{ill|Sakataike|ja|坂田池|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakataike|qq=|1=Sakataike|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11425526}}, {{ill|Toriikunuma|ja|鳥食沼|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toriikunuma|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (disappeared) * Reservoirs: {{ill|Jakagaike|ja|雀蛇ヶ池|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jakagaike|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, [[:en:Dongting Lake|Tōteiko]], {{ill|Konakaike|ja|小中池|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konakaike|qq=|1=Konaka Pond|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11458767}} * Canals: {{ill|Great Tone Canal|ja|大利根用水|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great Tone Canal|qq=|1=Ōtone irrigation canal|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11433046}}, {{ill|Ryōsō Canal|ja|両縄用水|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryōsō Canal|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Bōsō Conduit|ja|房羽導水路|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bōsō Conduit|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} * Fishing Ports: {{ill|Iioka Fishing Port|ja|飼おか渡船港|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iioka Fishing Port|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Kuriyama River Fishing Port|ja|栗山川港|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuriyama River Fishing Port|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Katakai Fishing Port|ja|片谷港|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katakai Fishing Port|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
Central Kujukuri Plain contains midstream wetlands of the Kuriyama River, remnants of Jōmon-period {{ill|lagoon|ja|湖沼|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lagoon|qq=|1=still waters|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q337567}}s, known as the Kuriyama River Wetlands. This area hosts endangered wetland plant species but has rapidly decreased due to {{ill|Meiji-period development|ja|明治期高速開発|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji-period development|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.<ref group="note">While many lagoons once existed in the Kujukuri Plain, few remain in the Kuriyama River midstream, bordered by [[:en:Tako, Chiba|Tako Town]] in the south, {{ill|Sōsa|ja|匿哲市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōsa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in the northwest, and [[:en:Yokoshibahikari|Yokoshibahikari]] in the north.</ref> The {{ill|Narutō-Tōgane Carnivorous Plant Community|ja|成東東金食虫植物群落|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Narutō-Tōgane Carnivorous Plant Community|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 成東・東金食虫植物群落|1=Naruto-Togane Area Carnivorous Plant Field|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11495489}} in [[:en:Sanmu|Sanmu]] near the Tōgane-Sakuta river boundary is a National Natural Monument. Dr. Tomitarō Makino, a botanist, praised the {{ill|Mobara-Hachitsumi Wetlands|ja|茂原八積水原|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mobara-Hachitsumi Wetlands|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} as a "treasure trove of plants."
=== Naya Settlements === The Kujukuri Plain has unique {{ill|Naya Settlement Patterns|ja|納屋集落|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naya Settlement Patterns|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Villages and farmland alternate in a linear pattern parallel to the coastline. These settlements started when fishermen near coasts transitioned to farmers and built [[:en:Barn|Naya warehouses]] to store gear. Later, as coastlines retreated, they settled permanently. During consolidation into broader towns, such as [[:en:Yokoshiba, Chiba|Yokoshiba Town]], the shape of their municipal areas often remained elongated.<ref name="kd" />
